Dating: LATE PERIOD (not before); PTOLEMAIC PERIOD (not after)
Name: Head of a king
Description: This sculptors model has suffered much damage. The lateral parts  of the "nemes" are missing, the nose is broken and of the uraeus, which shone on the forehead of the king, now only remains a small amorphous block. The piece is probably a cast, seeing that the head is hollowed out.
